12/07/2009
ATHENS, Greece -- A small homemade time bomb exploded on Saturday (July 11th) in Athens outside the home of former Deputy Interior Minister Panagiotis Hinofotis, media reported.
The explosion cars parked outside the building, but caused no injuries.
The attack followed three warning phone calls to the police and a TV broadcaster.
Police suspect a terrorist group was responsible for the bombing.
(ANA-MPA, Kathimerini, In.news, AFP, Reuters, AP - 11/07/09)
